      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/64/1356",
      "text": [
        ": «مَا مِنْ عَبْدٍ يَقْرَأُ آخِرَ اَلْكَهْفِ حِينَ يَنَامُ إِلاَّ اِسْتَيْقَظَ مِنْ مَنَامِهِ فِي اَلسَّاعَةِ اَلَّتِي يُرِيدُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1356 - Amir ibn Abdullah ibn Juza'ah narrated from Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) who said:\n\"There is no servant who recites the end of Surah al-Kahf before sleeping except that they will wake up at the hour they desire.\""
        ]
      }
